    "date": "2017-11-15",
    "comment": "Rationale: Authors show that induction of NMDAR-LTD by low-frequency stimulation (900stimuli at 1Hz) at CA1 synapses requires STAT3. To test this, they used pharmacological blockade of STAT3 by application of two different compounds, Stattic and STA-21, and a sh-RNA-mediated downregulation of STAT3 protein levels. In both scenarios, NMDAR-LTD induction is prevented, which suggests the involvement of STAT3 in NMDAR-LTD.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n-Hippocampal organotypic slices were prepared from 8-day-old Wistar rats.\n-shRNAs against rat STAT3 were synthesized.",
